tafsir[16]{c,v,t}:
  83,7,"No indeed; the Book of the libertines is in Sijjin;"
  83,8,"and what shall teach thee what is Sijjin?"
  83,9,"A book inscribed."
  83,11,"who cry lies to the Day of Doom;"
  83,12,"and none cries lies to it but every guilty aggressor."
  83,14,"No indeed; but that they were earning has rusted upon their hearts."
  83,16,"then they shall roast in Hell."
  83,18,"No indeed; the book of the pious is in Illiyun;"
  83,19,"and what shall teach thee what is Illiyun?"
  83,21,"witnessed by those brought nigh."
  83,23,"upon couches gazing;"
  83,24,"thou knowest in their faces the radiancy of bliss"
  83,25,"as they are given to drink of a wine sealed"
  83,26,"whose seal is musk -- so after that let the strivers strive --"
  83,28,"a fountain at which do drink those brought nigh."
  83,33,"Yet they were not sent as watchers over them."